# Changed-files review — session-19 design fix (Curbside Commons)

You are the adversarial reviewer. Review ONLY the diff below (40 insertions, 2 files) against the stated defect and the project bars. Verdict: APPROVE or REVISE with numbered findings (P1/P2/P3). Refute-or-fix stance; do not restate the diff.

## The defect (measured, on the release candidate 43efc55)
/fees findings' evidence receipts use a shared 4-track CSS grid `.rpt-receipts` (2.1fr/1fr/1.35fr/0.9fr). The 4th cell "the arithmetic" carries sentence-length evidence but got the smallest track: measured 48px wide, wrapping 13-17 lines of one-syllable ribbons, at ALL desktop widths (1280/1440/1728). 9 affected cells; "THE ARITHMETIC" dt itself clipped. /report and /demo share the same classes but hold short ids — measured zero ribbon cells there. Print (Letter ~816px) uses the <=900px 2-col fold and reads perfectly; print page-breaks orphaned the BASIS rail label.

## The fix (in the diff)
1. globals.css: `.fee-wrap .rpt-receipts` scoped override -> 2-col grid (statement+clause / rule+arithmetic), plus `.fee-wrap .rpt-rc:nth-child(odd)` border/padding reset (the exact pattern the <=900 breakpoint already uses). /report and /demo untouched.
2. globals.css @media print: `.rpt-rail { break-after: avoid }` + `.rpt-sec { break-inside: avoid }` (oversize sections still break naturally per CSS spec).
3. evals/e2e/fees.spec.ts: new tooth — at 1280 every `#fee-report .rpt-rc dd` bounding box must be >=150px wide. RED proven against the old artifact (fails at width 48); GREEN on the fixed tree (dev e2e 27/27 incl. axe zero A/AA x6 surfaces; vitest 1240+7; build 58/58).

## Bars
- No content/copy change, no color change, CSS layout + one test only.
- The 2x2 receipts must not regress /report or /demo (scoped selector — verify the scoping holds).
- e2e runs in BOTH modes (dev + artifact); the new test uses setViewportSize — flag if that conflicts with either mode's config.
- Flag anything the fix misses (e.g., other .fee-wrap grids, the nth-child(odd) assumption vs the DOM order of the 4 .rpt-rc cells, dt wrapping at the new widths).

## The diff
