1-rule-table.draft.json#0","file":"docs/research/uc1-rule-table.draft.json","anchor":"uc1-rule-table.draft.json (part 1)","text":"{\n  \"$schema_note\": \"Draft rule table for UC-1 (NYC fee-cap audit). Schema is of our design and is documented inline in docs/research/uc1-rule-table.md §'JSON schema'. NOT wired into lib/packs/fees/ — that is slice F1. This file is a research artifact, human-readable, provider-agnostic.\",\n  \"meta\": {\n    \"jurisdiction\": \"US-NY-NYC\",\n    \"statute\": \"NYC Administrative Code § 20-563.3 (Fee caps), Subchapter 36 (Third-Party Food Delivery Services)\",\n    \"amending_law\": \"Local Law 79 of 2025 (Council Int. No. 762-B of 2024)\",\n    \"enacted_became_law_date\": \"2025-05-31\",\n    \"effective_date\": \"2025-06-30\",\n    \"effective_date_status\": \"VERIFIED_PRIMARY\",\n    \"supersedes\": \"Local Law 103 of 2021 baseline of § 20-563.3\",\n    \"cap_base_term\": \"purchase price of each online order\",\n    \"cap_base_definition_status\": \"UNVERIFIED\",\n    \"as_of\": \"2026-07-03\",\n    \"source_primary\": \"Enacted LL79/2025 certified PDF via intro.nyc/local-laws/2025-79 (pdftotext); Legistar Int 0762-2024 action history\",\n    \"quarantine\": \"All sources treated as untrusted data per Law 11; facts extracted only.\",\n    \"coverage_disclaimer\": \"Codifies enforceable constraints found in § 20-563.3 as amended. Does NOT claim to cover all edge cases or the full Subchapter 36. Penalty/restitution provisions live outside this section (UNVERIFIED).\"\n  },\n  \"definitions\": [\n    { \"term\": \"delivery_fee\", \"ref\": \"§ 20-563 (as amended by LL79 §1)\", \"text\": \"fee for a service delivering food to customers within at least 1 mile of the establishment\", \"status\": \"VERIFIED_PRIMARY\" },\n    { \"term\": \"basic_service_fee\", \"ref\": \"§ 20-563 (LL79 §2)\", \"text\": \"fee for a service that (i) lets the establishment receive delivery/pickup orders on all of the platform's sites/apps and (ii) makes it searchable/discoverable by name in relevant results\", \"status\": \"VERIFIED_PRIMARY\" },\n    { \"term\": \"enhanced_service_fee\", \"ref\": \"§ 20-563 (LL79 §2)\", \"text\": \"fee for a service other than what basic-service/delivery/transaction fees cover\", \"status\": \"VERIFIED_PRIMARY\" },\n    { \"term\": \"transaction_fee\", \"ref\": \"§ 20-563 (LL100/2021 baseline; unchanged label)\", \"text\": \"fee related to processing the online order\", \"status\": \"PARTIAL_verbatim_definition_not_re-extracted\" },\n    { \"term\": \"exigent_circumstances\", \"ref\": \"§ 20-563 (LL79 §2)\", \"text\": \"circumstances outside the platform's control, such as severe weather or natural disasters\", \"status\": \"VERIFIED_PRIMARY\" }\n  ],\n  \"fee_categories\": [\"delivery_fee\", \"basic_service_fee\", \"transaction_fee\", \"enhanced_service_fee\"],\n  \"rules\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"NYC-563.3-a-1\",\n      \"source_clause\": \"§ 20-563.3(a)\",","tokens":401},"score":15.190463824998787,"rank":4},{"chunk":{"id":"docs/GLOSSARY.md#19","file":"docs/GLOSSARY.md","anchor":"Glossary · Purchase price base","text":"| **Purchase price base** | \"Purchase price of each online order\" — the statutory base every cap percentage is measured against (§20-563.3(a)–(d)). Its inclusions/exclusions (tax, tip, pre- vs post-discount) are UNVERIFIED as of 2026-07-03 (source-memo U1) — base-derived verdicts are provisional until resolved. | The order amount the percentages apply to — with an honest asterisk: exactly what counts inside it is still an open question. |\n| **Reconciliation** | The operational process of comparing two independent records of the same activity (e.g., POS sales vs platform payout statement) and explaining every difference. | Lining up two versions of the books and accounting for every mismatch, penny by penny. |\n| **Recorded model turn** | A committed, typed decision (`evals/crew/cases/recorded-turns.json`) replayed in place of a live model call during offline trajectory evaluation; an unplanned turn throws loudly rather than defaulting. Steered/hostile recorded turns deliberately simulate a compromised model so what gets measured is the ORCHESTRATOR'S containment. | The \"AI's answer\" comes from a checked-in answer sheet — including some deliberately WRONG answers, to prove the guardrails catch a misbehaving AI. |","tokens":236},"score":15.1086311022116,"rank":5}],"answered":true,"answer_span":"| The \"being listed and findable on the app\" fee — max 5%.","citations":[{"file":"docs/GLOSSARY.md","anchor":"Glossary · Asserted pass-through (unverified)","span":"| **Asserted pass-through (unverified)** | The fee-audit verdict state `asserted-passthrough-unverified` (M2, 2026-07-04): a transaction fee above the 3% cap whose §20-563.3(c)(i)–(ii) pass-through exception rests solely on the platform's own `passthroughDocumented` flag. The statement cannot verify the fee equals the actual processor charge, so the audit surfaces the reliance as a non-gating warn — neither silently cleared nor called a violation. | The platform says an over-3% card fee is \"just passing on the real card cost.\" The bill alone can't prove that either way, so the checker flags it for follow-up instead of trusting it or accusing anyone. |\n| **Audit trail** | An append-only, structured record of every action, decision, and actor in the system, sufficient to reconstruct what happened and why. | A tamper-evident logbook: who did what, when, and on what evidence. |\n| **Basic service fee** | NYC §20-563 (as amended by LL79/2025): the fee for the service that lets a food service establishment receive delivery/pick-up orders on all the platform's sites and be prominently searchable; capped at 5% of the purchase price per order, or on the calendar-month average (§20-563.3(b)). | The \"being listed and findable on the app\" fee — max 5%. |"}],"score":16.163425869296965},"poisonRetrieved":false}
